## Transfer Impact Assessment (TIA) — transfers to the USA

Since data importers in the **USA** are involved, a **Transfer Impact
Assessment** must be documented following Schrems II (CJEU C-311/18) and the
DSK assessment "Data transfers to the USA" (2023):

1. **Legal situation in the recipient country:** US government access via FISA 702 / EO 12333
2. **Data Privacy Framework (DPF):** check per service whether it is listed as
   DPF-certified with the US Department of Commerce (https://www.dataprivacyframework.gov/list)
3. **Supplementary safeguards:** encryption in transit (TLS 1.2+) AND at rest
   with customer control of the keys; pseudonymisation prior to transfer
4. **Risk assessment:** which data categories go where — sensitive
   categories (Art. 9 GDPR) require a stricter assessment

TIA documentation: separate internal report; to be presented during audits.
